### NexusAI Gateway — Example HTTP Requests
### Compatible with IntelliJ HTTP Client and VS Code REST Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@token = REPLACE_WITH_TOKEN_FROM_LOGIN

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# AUTH
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Register a new company account (creates tenant + admin user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "companyName": "Acme Corp",
  "email": "admin@acme.com",
  "password": "secret1234"
}

### 2. Login with existing account
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@acme.com",
  "password": "secret1234"
}

### 3. Register — validation error (password too short)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "companyName": "Bad Corp",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "password": "short"
}

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# USERS  (requires Bearer token)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4. Get current user profile (/me)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. List all users in the same tenant (ADMIN only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Access protected endpoint without token → 403
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# HEALTH / INFRA
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### 7. Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/health

### 8. Swagger UI (open in browser)
# http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI GATEWAY  (requires Bearer token)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### 9. Simple chat — no sensitive data
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What are the main benefits of using an AI gateway in a corporate environment?"
}

### 10. Chat with CPF in prompt — DLP masks it before sending to LLM
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "The customer with CPF 123.456.789-00 is requesting a refund. What is the standard process?"
}

### 11. Chat with email in prompt — DLP masks it
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Send a follow-up to joao.silva@empresa.com.br about the pending invoice."
}

### 12. Chat with multiple sensitive fields — all masked
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Client João, CPF 987.654.321-00, phone (11) 98765-4321, card 4111 1111 1111 1111. Please summarize this profile."
}

### 13. Chat with custom system prompt
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Explain what a JWT token is.",
  "systemPrompt": "You are a technical mentor for junior developers. Keep explanations simple and add code examples."
}

### 14. Chat — message too long → 400 validation error
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": ""
}

### 15. Chat — no token → 403
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "This should fail."
}

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# RAG — Document Management  (requires Bearer token)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### 16. Upload a TXT document
# Use IntelliJ's multipart support or curl:
# curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/rag/documents \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
#   -F "file=@/path/to/document.txt"
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/rag/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary

--boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="company-policy.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

NexusAI Gateway is our corporate AI platform.
All data sent to external LLMs is first scanned for sensitive information.
CPFs, emails, phone numbers, and credit card numbers are automatically redacted.
The system supports multiple tenants, each with isolated data.
--boundary--

### 17. List uploaded documents for current tenant
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/rag/documents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 18. Chat WITH RAG context (default — useRag: null treated as true)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What does the company do with sensitive data before sending to the LLM?"
}

### 19. Chat WITHOUT RAG (explicitly skip context enrichment)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/ai/chat
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What is the capital of Brazil?",
  "useRag": false
}

### 20. Delete a document (removes all chunks + embeddings)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/rag/documents/company-policy.txt
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
